The paper proposes a new method for solving inverse problems using deep learning techniques. The method involves learning an end-to-end mapping from observed data to the ground-truth, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of regularization techniques, which are commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses the flexibility of the proposed network structure, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
